            <div class="flex items-start">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-gradient-to-br from-primary-500 to-primary-600 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold text-lg">
                  1
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="ml-6">
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Bank Account Opening (Personal & Business)</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                  Comprehensive support for opening Zurich bank accounts: personal accounts for salary and expenses, business accounts for entrepreneurs and company directors, multi-currency accounts for international transactions. Agencies guide choice between traditional banks and neobanks based on needs. Traditional bank setup (UBS, Credit Suisse, Raiffeisen, PostFinance): coordinate appointments at Zurich branches (Paradeplatz, Bahnhofstrasse, local offices), prepare complete documentation (passport, permit, employment contract, address proof), accompany to appointments for support, explain account features (debit/credit cards, online banking, investment options), negotiate fees and minimum balances. Neobank setup (Yapeal, Neon): guide app download and registration, assist with document uploads, troubleshoot verification issues, explain digital banking features, coordinate physical card delivery. For Revolut users: clarify Swiss acceptance, advise on complementary Swiss account needed for salary (IBAN requirement), optimize multi-currency setup. Business accounts: coordinate with employers or company registration, meet business banking requirements, set up corporate cards and expense management.
                </p>
                <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                  <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-primary-50 text-primary-700 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Traditional Banks</span>
                  <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-primary-50 text-primary-700 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Neobanks</span>
                  <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-primary-50 text-primary-700 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Business Accounts</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-100 hover:shadow-xl transition-shadow duration-300">
            <div class="flex items-start">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-gradient-to-br from-primary-500 to-primary-600 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold text-lg">
                  2
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="ml-6">
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Introductions to Expat-Friendly Banks</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                  Agencies leverage relationships with Zurich banks providing expat-friendly services. Neobanks: Yapeal (Swiss digital bank, English interface, instant onboarding, CHF + multi-currency, sustainability focus, perfect for immediate banking needs), Neon (Swiss digital bank, free account, cashback, excellent for students/young professionals), Revolut (multi-currency champion, real-time exchange, international transfers, crypto support, complement to Swiss account). Traditional banks with expat services: UBS (Switzerland's largest, expat banking divisions, English-speaking relationship managers, wealth management from CHF 250,000, premium accounts with investment platforms), Credit Suisse (private banking for HNWI, expat advisory, global investment access, English support at major Zurich branches), Raiffeisen (cooperative bank, competitive rates, local presence across Zurich, some English services, good for mortgages). Agencies explain pros/cons: neobanks for speed and convenience, traditional banks for comprehensive services (mortgages, investments, business banking), hybrid approach using both. Facilitate warm introductions to relationship managers, explain Swiss banking culture (discretion, conservatism, long-term relationships), negotiate better terms leveraging agency relationships.
                </p>
                <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                  <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-primary-50 text-primary-700 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Yapeal</span>
                  <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-primary-50 text-primary-700 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Neon</span>
                  <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-primary-50 text-primary-700 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Revolut</span>
